WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.418
Previously on "Stumptown"...

00:03.420 --> 00:04.705
Grey: Ansel likes cars.
He wants to drive.

00:04.710 --> 00:06.496
Maybe he's sick of having people
drive him around all the time.

00:06.500 --> 00:07.660
Tookie: What's up?

00:07.670 --> 00:10.537
Tookie, Grey left me
in charge. I need your help.

00:10.540 --> 00:12.747
Tookie: The meal I'm about
to prepare Just for you.

00:12.750 --> 00:14.377
Tacos chicharon.

00:14.380 --> 00:16.575
"The mole was delicious
and well-prepared."

00:16.580 --> 00:18.207
Chaz: I'm in this crew.
We steal cars.

00:18.210 --> 00:20.166
We didn't know that
the van had drugs in it.

00:20.170 --> 00:21.910
Lee: Chaz's attorney is here.
He posted bail.

00:21.920 --> 00:23.569
Thank you, Detective.

00:23.580 --> 00:25.207
See you in court, Dad.

00:27.540 --> 00:30.668
[ Classical version
of "I Melt with You" plays ]

00:30.670 --> 00:33.491
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:45.380 --> 00:47.200
Officiant: Please rise.

00:48.960 --> 00:50.530
Gah! Oof!

00:50.540 --> 00:51.495
[ Grunts ]

00:59.710 --> 01:01.166
[ Grunts ]
Aah!

01:07.420 --> 01:08.660
Grab her, grab her!

01:08.670 --> 01:09.989
Hey!
Aah!

01:10.000 --> 01:13.072
Zack and Jenna have chosen
to write their own vows.

01:13.080 --> 01:15.036
Before you share them,
though,

01:15.040 --> 01:17.452
I need to confirm
your intentions here today.

01:17.460 --> 01:20.167
Do you, Jenna,
agree to take this man --

01:20.170 --> 01:21.569
[ Door bursts open ]
Dex: Stop! Wait!

01:21.580 --> 01:24.743
Stop! Don't do it!
[ Spectators gasp, music stops ]

01:24.750 --> 01:26.035
[ Panting ]

01:34.670 --> 01:35.534
Tookie: Rip it off!

01:35.540 --> 01:37.167
Okay.

01:37.170 --> 01:38.114
Ta-da!
Ta-da!

01:39.460 --> 01:41.280
Say hello
to your new kitchen!

01:41.290 --> 01:42.780
Oh, I have a kitchen --
without wheels.

01:42.790 --> 01:43.996
You have a room

01:44.000 --> 01:45.820
that does a cruel impersonation
of a kitchen.

01:45.830 --> 01:47.036
It's a toy piano.

01:47.040 --> 01:49.031
_ This is _
a Viennese forteplano,

01:49.040 --> 01:50.746
and I will be
your Mozart.

01:50.750 --> 01:52.160
The grease trap
smells funky.

01:52.170 --> 01:53.819
The maestro's busy,
Victor!

01:53.830 --> 01:55.457
I know
what you're thinking.

01:55.460 --> 01:57.166
"Tookie,
the streets need you."

01:57.170 --> 01:58.319
[ Laughs ]
Oh, is that what I'm thinking?

01:58.330 --> 01:59.820
That's why this is
the perfect solution.

01:59.830 --> 02:01.320
I'm still mobile,

02:01.330 --> 02:02.786
I'm still the king
of the street food scene.

02:02.790 --> 02:04.951
But your bar can serve up
legit cuisine for once.

02:04.960 --> 02:06.325
Okay.

02:06.330 --> 02:07.786
I just
need to serve food

02:07.790 --> 02:09.610
that's salty enough to
keep people drinking, Maestro.

02:09.620 --> 02:11.451
That's it.

02:11.460 --> 02:12.779
You hate it?

02:15.580 --> 02:17.377
No, I don't hate it,
Ansel.

02:17.380 --> 02:19.701
It's just --
it's a surprise, is all.

02:23.080 --> 02:24.661
Alright.
Let's do this.

02:24.670 --> 02:26.877
Why don't we try it out
for a week and see what happens?

02:26.880 --> 02:28.780
[ Laughing ] Yes!
Victor, start up the grill!

02:28.790 --> 02:30.246
Tacos for
my new partner.

02:30.250 --> 02:32.161
I didn't say partner.
We're not partners.

02:34.080 --> 02:35.820
[ Groans ]
[ Laughs ]

02:35.830 --> 02:36.819
[ Upbeat music plays ]

02:36.830 --> 02:38.878
Hey.
You could've warned me.

02:38.880 --> 02:40.199
[ Chuckles ]
What? Come on.

02:40.210 --> 02:41.780
I mean,
i-it's a no-brainer.

02:41.790 --> 02:44.372
Now I get free tacos
with my free beer.

02:44.380 --> 02:46.826
Hey, Dex, how 'bout
ifI redecorated your house

02:46.830 --> 02:47.706
when you weren't home?

02:47.710 --> 02:49.075
Could you please?

02:49.080 --> 02:51.036
I'm so sick
of my parents' old furniture.

02:51.040 --> 02:53.497
Okay, what if
I traded in your car?

02:53.500 --> 02:55.161
How dare you.

02:55.170 --> 02:57.456
That Mustang is the soul
of this whole operation.

02:57.460 --> 02:59.109
I know,
and this is my bar.

02:59.120 --> 03:01.497
It's the only thing I've
ever had that's really mine.

03:01.500 --> 03:03.070
[Telephone rings ]

03:03.080 --> 03:05.287
[ Receiver clicks ]

03:05.290 --> 03:06.416
Hello. Bad Alibi.

03:07.670 --> 03:10.571
Yeah, she's, uh --
she's right here.

03:10.580 --> 03:11.615
For me?

03:11.620 --> 03:12.917
For you.
Thank you.

03:15.750 --> 03:17.706
Stumptown Investigations.
You got Dex.

03:19.120 --> 03:20.496
Uh, yeah,
I'm free today.

03:20.500 --> 03:22.821
Um, why don't you come down
to the Bad Alibi?

03:22.830 --> 03:24.411
It's in --
Fire! Fire!!

03:24.420 --> 03:25.375
You said fire?!

03:25.380 --> 03:26.665
Fire!
North --

03:28.670 --> 03:29.910
[Air hissing ]
I'm -- I'm sorry.
What?

03:29.920 --> 03:31.490
iAyuda!

03:32.500 --> 03:34.286
iAyuda!

03:34.290 --> 03:35.780
Actually,
I'll come to you.

03:35.790 --> 03:38.111
iAyuda!

03:38.120 --> 03:41.169
[ Rock music plays ]

03:41.170 --> 03:44.617
[ Brakes squeal, engine clunks ]

03:44.620 --> 03:47.783
These are beautiful,
but I really don't care

03:47.790 --> 03:50.827
what the guests expect
the cake to look like, Claire.

03:50.830 --> 03:52.741
I mean, this bakery
makes a difference, okay?

03:52.750 --> 03:54.820
They -- They give
formerly incarcerated people

03:54.830 --> 03:56.036
culinary experience.

03:56.040 --> 03:58.167
They give them a chance
to get back on their feet.

03:58.170 --> 04:00.206
[ Door opens ]
It's your wedding day,
Jenna.

04:00.210 --> 04:02.371
If you want a convict cake,
I will get you a convict cake.
[ Door closes ]

04:02.380 --> 04:04.166
Thank you.

04:04.170 --> 04:05.785
Hi.
Are you from the bakery?

04:05.790 --> 04:07.075
Uh, Dex Parios,
private --

04:07.080 --> 04:08.206
Security consultant.

04:09.170 --> 04:10.455
Yes.

04:10.460 --> 04:12.576
Okay.

04:12.580 --> 04:14.286
That seems a little
over the top, ClaIre,

04:14.290 --> 04:15.871
even for you.

04:15.880 --> 04:18.246
[ Chuckles ] Sorry. She's always
trying to protect me.

04:18.250 --> 04:20.377
Emphasis on the trying.

04:20.380 --> 04:22.416
You asked me to plan
your big day. Let me handle it.

04:23.620 --> 04:25.497
I really am
very grateful.
Ohh.

04:25.500 --> 04:28.958
It's gonna be a perfect day.
I promise.

04:28.960 --> 04:30.609
Okay. Well, um,
it's nice to meet you.

04:30.620 --> 04:31.951
Mm-hmm.
Congratulations.

04:31.960 --> 04:33.871
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

04:33.880 --> 04:34.949
Hi.
Hello.

04:34.960 --> 04:36.370
Claire Chesterfield.

04:36.380 --> 04:38.280
Thanks so much
for driving out.

04:38.290 --> 04:40.611
I love starting a case
with a lie.

04:40.620 --> 04:42.668
No, uh, red flags there.
[ Chuckles ]

04:42.670 --> 04:45.161
Ohh. My sister.

04:45.170 --> 04:46.569
She is amazing.

04:46.580 --> 04:48.070
Mm.

04:48.080 --> 04:51.072
An "adopt every animal
at the shelter" type.

04:51.080 --> 04:52.957
Oh.
Sounds like my brother.

04:54.290 --> 04:57.498
Then you know
how vulnerable that makes her.

04:57.500 --> 04:59.411
She's rushing
to the altar

04:59.420 --> 05:01.160
because her fianc
needs a green card.

05:01.170 --> 05:02.740
Oh.
Well, that's not great.

05:02.750 --> 05:04.570
Yeah. It's my fault.

05:04.580 --> 05:07.458
I shouldn't have let us
drift apart.

05:07.460 --> 05:09.451
We're from St. Louis,
but Jenna moved out here

05:09.460 --> 05:11.746
a few years back
to get her master's,

05:11.750 --> 05:13.115
and then she calls me
out of the blue

05:13.120 --> 05:14.530
and says
she's getting married.

05:14.540 --> 05:16.872
A lot of marriages
are trial runs.

05:16.880 --> 05:18.450
You don't understand.

05:18.460 --> 05:20.576
She won't ask
for a prenup.

05:20.580 --> 05:22.992
The company board took a vote,
and they decided that

05:23.000 --> 05:24.991
if she goes through
with the marriage,

05:25.000 --> 05:26.911
she loses the shares
my parents left her.

05:26.920 --> 05:28.876
Oh.

05:28.880 --> 05:30.745
She walks away
from $125 million.

05:30.750 --> 05:32.661
[ Spits ]
Oh.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.571
Sorry.
That's okay.

05:36.580 --> 05:39.959
So, the -- the sod business
has done well for you all.

05:39.960 --> 05:42.872
I won't let my sister
ruin her life,

05:42.880 --> 05:45.417
not without knowing who
she's throwing it all away for.

05:45.420 --> 05:47.661
So you want me
to look into the groom.

05:47.670 --> 05:48.955
Someone has to.

05:48.960 --> 05:50.530
Jenna's too sweet
to look closely,

05:50.540 --> 05:52.451
and she doesn't even know
hIS given name.

05:52.460 --> 05:53.666
I'm sorry?

05:53.670 --> 05:57.071
Yeah, he fancies himself
some sort of an artist,

05:57.080 --> 06:00.038
uses a pseudonym --
Zack Knight.

06:00.040 --> 06:02.167
What kind of artist?

06:02.170 --> 06:07.415
See twin eagle birds
up in the tree
[Tattoo needle buzzing ]

06:07.420 --> 06:12.619
One for you,
and there's one for me

06:12.620 --> 06:17.489
When we thought
we might be losing our minds

06:17.500 --> 06:19.320
[ Buzzing stops ]
[ Irish accent]
And we're done.

06:19.330 --> 06:21.116
We saw the signs

06:21.120 --> 06:24.328
So, no hot tubs
for a week.

06:24.330 --> 06:27.208
Sleep on your belly
for a month.

06:27.210 --> 06:29.246
And if it goes
the bad kind of crusty, call me.

06:29.250 --> 06:30.569
[ Chuckles ]

06:30.580 --> 06:33.117
[Telephone rings ]

06:33.120 --> 06:35.281
[ Sighs ]

06:35.290 --> 06:36.370
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Yeah.

06:36.380 --> 06:37.529
Dex: Zack Knight?

06:37.540 --> 06:38.700
I'm your 4:00.

06:38.710 --> 06:39.699
Password?

06:39.710 --> 06:41.826
Irezumi?

06:41.830 --> 06:43.536
Am I saying that right?

06:43.540 --> 06:44.495
[ Buzzer ]

06:48.620 --> 06:50.918
3%»:\

06:50.920 --> 06:52.205
Appointments and passwords.

06:52.210 --> 06:54.781
You are a, uh, triclq man
to see, Mr. Knight.

06:54.790 --> 06:56.246
Zack.
Dex.

06:56.250 --> 06:58.036
Nice to meet you.
You, too.

06:58.040 --> 06:59.780
I could give you
the spiel --

06:59.790 --> 07:03.248
customer privacy,
the sanctity of solitude.

07:03.250 --> 07:06.663
Honestly, speakeasy vibe
lets me charge more.

07:06.670 --> 07:08.911
Ah.
Don't forget
to keep that covered up.

07:08.920 --> 07:09.955
[ Buzzer, door opens ]

07:09.960 --> 07:11.496
What can I do for you?

07:11.500 --> 07:13.536
Uh, I'm thinking about
getting a tattoo.

07:13.540 --> 07:14.666
Excellent.
Mm-hmm.

07:14.670 --> 07:15.910
Otherwise,
this would be awkward.

07:15.920 --> 07:17.114
Yeah.
Yeah.

07:17.120 --> 07:18.997
Yes, it would.
[ Chuckles ]

07:19.000 --> 07:20.456
What kind?

07:20.460 --> 07:23.202
Uh, a blackbird perched,
you know,

07:23.210 --> 07:24.780
sort of right here
on my shoulder.

07:24.790 --> 07:25.825
Okay.

07:25.830 --> 07:27.536
Why a blackbird?

07:27.540 --> 07:29.872
I'll answer that question
if you answer one of mine first.

07:29.880 --> 07:31.370
[ Chuckles ]

07:31.380 --> 07:33.780
That's a bold new paradigm
in customer relations.

07:33.790 --> 07:35.951
Oh.
Go on, then.

07:35.960 --> 07:38.497
Zack Knight --
is that your real name?

07:38.500 --> 07:41.162
You might never find

07:41.170 --> 07:43.491
How did you s-say
you found me, again?

07:43.500 --> 07:44.706
A friend of a friend.

07:44.710 --> 07:46.200
Mm.

07:46.210 --> 07:48.667
Designs start at
two grand.

07:48.670 --> 07:51.571
Guess the whole speakeasy vibe
is really working for you.

07:51.580 --> 07:52.911
Yeah.

07:52.920 --> 07:54.319
Price is a problem
for you?

07:54.330 --> 07:56.571
No, not if I get
what I pay for.

07:56.580 --> 07:59.879
Don't nobody wanna be lonely

07:59.880 --> 08:02.576
That your helmet?
Yeah. It is.

08:02.580 --> 08:04.036
Why a blackbird?

08:04.040 --> 08:06.326
Everybody oughta be loved
sometime

08:06.330 --> 08:07.786
You know,
I actually have this thing

08:07.790 --> 08:10.372
that I need
to go and do now.

08:10.380 --> 08:12.416
But, um,
are you around tomorrow?

08:12.420 --> 08:13.614
Yeah, I am.

08:13.620 --> 08:16.248
But if you walk out that door,
you won't come back.

08:16.250 --> 08:18.377
Uh, maybe
I'll surprise you.

08:18.380 --> 08:19.529
Bye.

08:42.170 --> 08:43.535
[ Camera clicks ]

08:43.540 --> 08:45.326
Needs more paprika.
[Jazz music plays ]

08:45.330 --> 08:47.207
No. No.
No-no, no, no.

08:47.210 --> 08:49.576
Uh, just a dash more.
No. A dash?

08:49.580 --> 08:51.912
No. I will concede a pinch,
alright? But a dash? No.

08:51.920 --> 08:53.205
Every Sunday
with this, Mom?

08:53.210 --> 08:55.075
Relinquish the paprika,
Lionel.

08:55.080 --> 08:56.877
Hey, he's home --

09:02.620 --> 09:03.666
Give me that.

09:03.670 --> 09:05.114
There you go.
Just stir that up.

09:05.120 --> 09:06.610
Yeah,
it's ruined now.

09:06.620 --> 09:07.609
Just taste it.

09:10.670 --> 09:12.240
You're welcome.

09:13.670 --> 09:15.740
So, um...
[ Clears throat ]

09:15.750 --> 09:18.412
...when are we gonna discuss
your conflict of interest?

09:18.420 --> 09:19.660
With paprika?

09:19.670 --> 09:22.161
No, with representing
a suspect that I arrested.

09:22.170 --> 09:23.740
Suspect you arrested.

09:23.750 --> 09:26.708
Sweetheart, how did we end up
with this son?

09:26.710 --> 09:28.575
Oh, neither of you want me
to answer that question.

09:30.000 --> 09:31.570
[ Both chuckle ]

09:33.790 --> 09:36.031
Listen, uh...
[ Clears throat ]

09:36.040 --> 09:38.076
I worked on that case
for weeks, Dad.

09:38.080 --> 09:40.036
It's my CI.
It's my arrest, alright?

09:40.040 --> 09:43.112
I took 20 kilos of heroin
off the street.

09:43.120 --> 09:45.452
It's a blatant conflict
for you to represent Chaz.

09:45.460 --> 09:47.496
_ An associate
IS gonna argue the case.

09:47.500 --> 09:49.115
With you puppeteering
from the sidelines.

09:49.120 --> 09:51.281
Charles' father is a friend
from the club, Miles.

09:51.290 --> 09:52.450
He asked for my help.

09:52.460 --> 09:54.781
So it's okay
for you to take on the rich punk

09:54.790 --> 09:56.246
but leave his boys behind?

09:56.250 --> 09:58.036
Funny -- you didn't seem
to mind so much

09:58.040 --> 09:59.280
when I did that for you.

09:59.290 --> 10:01.667
I was 17 years old.
[ Chuckles ]

10:01.670 --> 10:03.877
You were a punk kid
who thought he was invincible.

10:03.880 --> 10:06.417
Yeah, but there's a difference
between selling a little weed

10:06.420 --> 10:08.706
and stealing cars and dealing
heroin, and you know that.

10:08.710 --> 10:09.779
Alright.

10:09.790 --> 10:11.576
This is new
for all of us,

10:11.580 --> 10:13.878
the two of you
opposing each other on a case.

10:13.880 --> 10:15.609
Dad's the one
who chose --

10:17.380 --> 10:20.417
Do not let this ruin
family brunch.

10:21.670 --> 10:23.206
Now, Mama hungry.

10:23.210 --> 10:24.825
Let's eat.
Alright.

10:24.830 --> 10:27.537
Here you go.
My mother's secret recipe.

10:27.540 --> 10:29.531
[ Extreme's "Me Llama" plays ]

10:29.540 --> 10:30.575
There you go.

10:30.580 --> 10:33.242
Cuando me toca

10:33.250 --> 10:36.538
[ Door opens ]
Buen provecho.

10:36.540 --> 10:38.610
[ Laughs ] What's...

10:38.620 --> 10:40.372
It's been like this
all afternoon.

10:40.380 --> 10:43.281
We're the most popular thing to
hit Portland since legalization.

10:43.290 --> 10:45.167
Ah, I love a story
with a happy ending.

10:45.170 --> 10:46.706
No, Dex,
a happy beginning.

10:46.710 --> 10:48.371
Hey, Dex,
why don't you ask me

10:48.380 --> 10:50.575
how many free waters
I poured today?

10:50.580 --> 10:52.161
Ooh.
Guessing a lot.

10:52.170 --> 10:53.785
We've gone through
enough glasses

10:53.790 --> 10:56.167
I'm gonna have to hire
a second dishwasher.

10:56.170 --> 10:57.990
This was
a terrible idea.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.991
Well, you said you'd give it
a week, right?

11:00.000 --> 11:02.377
[ Laptop chimes ]
Yeah.

11:02.380 --> 11:04.166
Ooh, I got
Zack Knight's real name.

11:04.170 --> 11:06.035
It's Scott Thompson.
Bodng.

11:06.040 --> 11:07.496
I can see
why he changed it.

11:07.500 --> 11:10.879
Nobody's gonna pay two grand
to have a soccer dad ink them.

11:10.880 --> 11:12.074
Okay, what are you up to,
Scotty?

11:12.080 --> 11:13.456
Good talk.
[Taps bar ]

11:13.460 --> 11:14.609
Sorry.

11:14.620 --> 11:16.451
[ Laptop beeps ]

11:19.330 --> 11:21.070
Well, that's one reason
to stop a wedding.

11:26.290 --> 11:28.702
Yeah, I remember this case --
Dahlia Montgomery,

11:28.710 --> 11:30.280
killed in a hit-and-run
just over a year ago.

11:30.290 --> 11:32.576
Well, the mother was convinced
that the fianc did it,

11:32.580 --> 11:34.070
this guy
named Scott Thompson.

11:34.080 --> 11:36.617
As a tattoo artist,
he's known as Zack Knight.

11:36.620 --> 11:38.747
Yeah, we -- we brought him in,
put him through the wringer,

11:38.750 --> 11:40.957
but the treads on the scene
matched a Mercedes G-Wagen,

11:40.960 --> 11:42.450
and Scott Thompson rides
a motorcycle.

11:42.460 --> 11:44.109
Yeah, but he could've
hired someone.

11:44.120 --> 11:45.109
If he did,
he covered his tracks.

11:45.120 --> 11:46.826
Did you like him
for it?

11:46.830 --> 11:49.572
He had motive, and, you know,
Dahlia's family was from money,

11:49.580 --> 11:51.571
and, according to the mother,
he was furious

11:51.580 --> 11:53.320
after she rejected
his proposals.

11:53.330 --> 11:56.117
Well, he has a type.
His new fiance's
loaded, as well.

11:56.120 --> 11:58.418
Look, the -- the truth is,
9 times out of 10,

11:58.420 --> 12:00.069
hit-and-runs are done
by a total stranger.

12:00.080 --> 12:02.071
That's why they're
the toughest cases to close.

12:02.080 --> 12:03.377
Kasra:
Detective Hoffman.

12:03.380 --> 12:06.668
DDA Valerie Kasra,
Dex Parios.

12:06.670 --> 12:08.956
Dex is an investigator
and friend of the department.

12:08.960 --> 12:10.996
Yes, I've seen your name
on my evidence list.

12:11.000 --> 12:12.319
You do very good work.

12:12.330 --> 12:13.570
Got a card?

12:13.580 --> 12:14.990
Oh. Yes, I do.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.069
[ Chuckles ]

12:16.080 --> 12:17.957
Um -- Oh. Uh...
[ Coins jingle ]

12:17.960 --> 12:18.745
Sorry. Um...
That's alright.

12:18.750 --> 12:19.819
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

12:19.830 --> 12:21.616
Ah.

12:21.620 --> 12:23.781
Uh, I just -- I --
This is my only one.

12:23.790 --> 12:25.451
You can take a...picture.

12:25.460 --> 12:26.449
Uh...

12:26.460 --> 12:28.166
Uh, you know what?
Take this.

12:28.170 --> 12:29.569
That's a coaster.

12:29.580 --> 12:32.071
Yeah, from a bar
that I use as my office.

12:33.040 --> 12:35.076
Okay. Thank you.

12:35.080 --> 12:36.616
See you.

12:36.620 --> 12:39.453
So, judge ruled against us
on conflict of interest.

12:39.460 --> 12:41.371
Your father's firm
can represent Chaz,

12:41.380 --> 12:43.416
so long as he's not the one
speaking in court.

12:43.420 --> 12:45.035
He's still gonna be the one
calling the shots.

12:45.040 --> 12:46.450
Oh, I'm aware.

12:46.460 --> 12:48.826
This is not my first go
against your father.

12:48.830 --> 12:50.320
So we better
be ready for him.

12:50.330 --> 12:53.242
Alright. Let me
run you through the case.

12:53.250 --> 12:55.662
Oh, and we should probably
get ahead on juicing limes.

12:55.670 --> 12:57.911
My tacos are for sure
upping the margarita orders.

12:57.920 --> 13:00.411
We don't need limes.

13:00.420 --> 13:03.162
No. Tell me you do not serve
that sugar swill.

13:03.170 --> 13:04.956
The people deserve better.

13:04.960 --> 13:06.951
Partner. We got to up
your margarita game.

13:06.960 --> 13:09.110
Ansel, go pick us up
6 pounds of limes.

13:09.120 --> 13:11.611
No, Ansel, stay here.
Prep the bar like you always do.

13:14.040 --> 13:16.076
The mix does taste bad.

13:16.080 --> 13:17.536
Well,
that's 'cause it's cheap.

13:17.540 --> 13:19.201
But this is
a beer and whiskey bar, okay?

13:19.210 --> 13:20.950
And I've learned,
as the owner,

13:20.960 --> 13:23.576
if you have too many
fresh ingredients,
they end up spoiling.

13:23.580 --> 13:26.117
I'm all for cutting costs,
but let's not compromise taste.

13:26.120 --> 13:28.702
Fill the Belvedere with Tito's
and the Grey Goose with Stoli.

13:28.710 --> 13:30.996
Well, that's illegal.
Right up your alley,
Stripes.

13:31.000 --> 13:33.912
Look, we need
a company brainstorming sesh.

13:33.920 --> 13:37.321
When this mind starts...
ticking,

13:37.330 --> 13:40.322
you never know
what gems will come from it.

13:40.330 --> 13:42.878
Great. Let's do it a little bit
later. I got some work to do.

13:42.880 --> 13:44.780
What's his usual timing
on later?

13:44.790 --> 13:46.872
5 minutes? 20?
An hour?

13:46.880 --> 13:48.529
I'll give him an hour.

13:48.540 --> 13:49.825
You came back.

13:49.830 --> 13:51.741
Yeah, surprised?
Happily.

13:51.750 --> 13:53.741
Most people who walk out
lose their nerve.

13:53.750 --> 13:54.956
Well, I almost did.

13:54.960 --> 13:57.372
I've never been able
to pull a trigger on a tattoo,

13:57.380 --> 13:59.871
which is weird_
because I'm a Marine.

13:59.880 --> 14:00.915
That is weird.

14:00.920 --> 14:02.956
Ever feel like_
you missed your Window,

14:02.960 --> 14:05.417
where something
wouldn't be a big deal at first

14:05.420 --> 14:08.708
and as time goes by, the more
it feels like a big deal?

14:08.710 --> 14:10.075
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

14:10.080 --> 14:12.116
My ma
gave me a watch once,

14:12.120 --> 14:14.452
and 1-1 broke it
within a week.

14:14.460 --> 14:16.576
I should've just told her
right away.

14:16.580 --> 14:18.912
Now I have to keep
making up elaborate excuses

14:18.920 --> 14:20.069
as to why
I'm never wearing it.

14:20.080 --> 14:22.571
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, exactly.

14:22.580 --> 14:23.911
Mm.
[ Clears throat ]

14:23.920 --> 14:25.785
Why don't I sketch up
this blackbird,

14:25.790 --> 14:27.576
see if it matches _
what's in your imagination?

14:27.580 --> 14:28.786
Sure.
Okay.

14:28.790 --> 14:30.496
That sounds great.
Thanks.

14:30.500 --> 14:31.740
So, when did you serve?

14:31.750 --> 14:33.570
Uh, 12 years ago.

14:33.580 --> 14:34.740
What'd you do?

14:34.750 --> 14:36.991
Intelligence mostly,
interrogations.

14:38.210 --> 14:39.825
It's not
what people think it is.

14:39.830 --> 14:41.206
Do your job,

14:41.210 --> 14:42.996
you're -- you're never
looking for answers.

14:43.000 --> 14:45.571
You're -- You're looking
for confirmation.

14:45.580 --> 14:46.786
Yeah?
Yeah.

14:46.790 --> 14:49.668
Personally, I-I like
to get people calm,

14:49.670 --> 14:52.707
have them underestimate me,
and then surprise them.

14:52.710 --> 14:55.873
It's hard for people to lie
when they're on the spot.

14:55.880 --> 14:58.075
For instance, did you kill
Dahlia Montgomery?

15:03.250 --> 15:04.990
[ Book slams ]
What is this?

15:05.000 --> 15:06.456
Dahlia came from money.

15:06.460 --> 15:08.496
Marrying her
would've set you up nicely.

15:08.500 --> 15:10.570
But Dahlia refused
to marry you.

15:10.580 --> 15:11.820
Isn't that right?

15:11.830 --> 15:14.378
I don't know what your game is,
but I'm not playing.

15:14.380 --> 15:15.199
Did you kill her, Scott?

15:16.580 --> 15:17.911
Did you?

15:19.580 --> 15:20.911
Yeah.

15:22.250 --> 15:23.956
Yeah, I...

15:23.960 --> 15:24.949
I did.

15:31.080 --> 15:32.536
We had a fight
about curtains.

15:32.540 --> 15:34.076
[ Sighs ]

15:34.080 --> 15:36.378
Dahlia wanted
these expenswe de5igner ones,

15:36.380 --> 15:38.280
and I just thought it was
to impress her mom, you know?

15:40.580 --> 15:42.457
And it just spiraled.

15:42.460 --> 15:46.533
One minute,
we're talking about curtains,

15:46.540 --> 15:49.111
and then she's screaming at me,
and then I just --

15:50.710 --> 15:53.076
I said all these terrible things
about her family --

15:53.080 --> 15:56.322
about wealth,
how it can ruin people.

15:56.330 --> 15:59.037
She saw red,
said she needed space, and...

16:01.790 --> 16:04.327
I should have never
let her get in the car.

16:04.330 --> 16:07.037
If she hadn't been on the road
that night...

16:12.210 --> 16:14.326
I'm the reason
that Dahlia's dead.

16:21.290 --> 16:22.996
Moved on pretty fast,
yeah?

16:23.000 --> 16:25.571
[ Bottle thuds ]
Didn't mean to.

16:25.580 --> 16:27.571
Jenna and I met
when we were both vulnerable.

16:27.580 --> 16:28.660
Just happened.

16:28.670 --> 16:30.877
I wanted
to take it slow.

16:30.880 --> 16:32.370
Your green card.

16:32.380 --> 16:34.826
I was willing to move back
to Dublin, try long distance,

16:34.830 --> 16:37.162
but Jenna wanted
to start our lives together.

16:37.170 --> 16:38.740
So she proposed.

16:38.750 --> 16:41.378
I said yes.

16:41.380 --> 16:43.610
Maybe I shouldn't have.

16:45.540 --> 16:48.577
Um...

16:48.580 --> 16:51.242
I work for Jenna's family.

16:53.500 --> 16:56.537
They wanted to know
who she was marrying.

16:56.540 --> 16:58.280
You gonna tell them?

16:58.290 --> 17:01.327
That you blame yourself
for a...

17:01.330 --> 17:03.116
tragic accident?

17:03.120 --> 17:05.327
I put her on the road.

17:05.330 --> 17:07.070
[ Sighs ]

17:08.540 --> 17:10.076
Got another glass?

17:10.080 --> 17:13.379
Let me just say
that our client, Charles,

17:13.380 --> 17:16.031
is the true victim
mmmwm.

17:16.040 --> 17:19.248
And we will prove
that the Portland Police Bureau

17:19.250 --> 17:20.740
_had a_ vendetta
against this young man.

17:20.750 --> 17:22.320
Oh, here we go.

17:22.330 --> 17:23.911
And when they failed
to garner the evidence,

17:23.920 --> 17:25.740
they falsified it.

17:25.750 --> 17:27.411
They manipulated witnesses.

17:27.420 --> 17:30.457
The police broke the law here,
ladies and gentlemen,

17:30.460 --> 17:31.779
not this young man.

17:31.790 --> 17:33.326
Ugh.
He's grandstanding.

17:33.330 --> 17:34.991
None of this will hold up
in court.

17:35.000 --> 17:36.570
Yeah,
it doesn't have to.

17:36.580 --> 17:38.878
He's trying the case
in the media.

17:38.880 --> 17:41.110
Straight out of
the Lionel Hoffman playbook.

17:41.120 --> 17:42.747
I thought my dad
was a jackass.

17:42.750 --> 17:44.706
[ Sighs ]

17:49.170 --> 17:50.740
Well...[ Chuckles ]
So, tell me.

17:50.750 --> 17:52.490
Why a blackbird?

17:52.500 --> 17:53.876
Oh, no.

17:53.880 --> 17:55.780
I wasn't -- _
I wasn't being serious.

17:55.790 --> 17:59.078
That was a part
of my...very clever ruse.

17:59.080 --> 18:02.538
But you could've said anything,
and you said a blackbird.

18:02.540 --> 18:04.747
Uh, okay, um...

18:04.750 --> 18:06.035
[ Chuckles softly ]

18:08.210 --> 18:10.667
I got thrown out of a punk show,
and he caught me.

18:11.880 --> 18:13.450
He was very funny.

18:15.750 --> 18:18.116
He would, um...

18:18.120 --> 18:20.953
He would meet a stranger,
cold,

18:20.960 --> 18:24.327
and they would be laughing
hysterically within minutes,

18:24.330 --> 18:27.618
like deep "known you
my whole life" belly laughs.

18:27.620 --> 18:30.032
[ Chuckles ]

18:30.040 --> 18:34.033
Everyone wanted to be
Benjamin Blackbird's friend.

18:34.040 --> 18:36.497
But you got him.

18:36.500 --> 18:37.956
Yeah, I did.

18:37.960 --> 18:40.326
I did.

18:40.330 --> 18:43.379
Now he's gone.

18:43.380 --> 18:45.200
Yeah.

18:48.750 --> 18:50.240
I could've stopped it.

18:53.830 --> 18:56.162
[ Sighs, chuckles ]

18:56.170 --> 18:59.037
Uh...

18:59.040 --> 19:02.498
[Voice breaking ]
I had a ch--

19:02.500 --> 19:04.661
There was a choice
that I...

19:06.290 --> 19:08.827
[ Crying ] I had a chance
to stop it, you know?

19:08.830 --> 19:10.570
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

19:10.580 --> 19:12.821
[ Breathes deeply]

19:12.830 --> 19:14.570
[ Clears throat ]

19:17.540 --> 19:18.746
A dahlia.

19:18.750 --> 19:20.991
Mm-hmm.
It's nice.

19:21.000 --> 19:22.956
I think
you should get a tattoo.

19:22.960 --> 19:25.702
It's cathartic --
the pain.

19:25.710 --> 19:26.950
It's cleansing.

19:26.960 --> 19:28.530
Yeah, and then
you're walking around

19:28.540 --> 19:30.610
with the memory
of a corpse

19:30.620 --> 19:33.418
etched on your body,
I mean, forever.

19:33.420 --> 19:35.376
It's gonna be there no matter
if you can see it or not.

19:35.380 --> 19:36.369
Right?

19:38.290 --> 19:40.326
[ Inhales sharply ]
How do you do it?

19:40.330 --> 19:41.456
Do what?

19:41.460 --> 19:43.746
Move on,
try -- to try again.

19:43.750 --> 19:45.490
How do you d--
How do you do that?

19:45.500 --> 19:46.706
[ Sighs ]

19:46.710 --> 19:50.498
It helps to meet somebody
who -- who gets it.

19:55.040 --> 19:58.612
Jenna lost her husband a few
months before I lost Dahlia.

19:58.620 --> 19:59.871
Oh.

19:59.880 --> 20:01.780
She knows
how hard it is.

20:01.790 --> 20:04.076
Please don't tell me
you stopped checking your phone

20:04.080 --> 20:05.536
two days
before our wedding.

20:05.540 --> 20:07.371
I've been
texting you.

20:07.380 --> 20:08.369
So sorry.

20:08.380 --> 20:09.870
Totally lost track.

20:09.880 --> 20:11.745
[ Sighs ]
Sorry.

20:11.750 --> 20:13.786
The security consultant?

20:13.790 --> 20:15.746
Hey. Hi. It --

20:15.750 --> 20:17.115
What's going on here,
Zack?

20:17.120 --> 20:18.826
Nothing. Nothing.

20:18.830 --> 20:20.821
Uh, security thing.

20:20.830 --> 20:23.788
I just had to ask your fianc
just a couple of questions.

20:23.790 --> 20:25.371
With whiskey?

20:25.380 --> 20:28.076
Yeah, that's -- that's my fault.
I took it out.

20:28.080 --> 20:30.207
Come join us.

20:30.210 --> 20:32.610
Uh, one year sober,
but thanks.

20:32.620 --> 20:33.780
Ah. I see.

20:33.790 --> 20:37.908
I'm gonna...
get out of your hair.

20:37.920 --> 20:39.569
Congratulations
to you both.

20:39.580 --> 20:40.569
I'm sorry.

20:40.580 --> 20:42.377
No. No worries.
I'm sorry.

20:42.380 --> 20:43.916
I'm so on edge
these days.

20:43.920 --> 20:46.070
It's like, the closer we get
to our big day,

20:46.080 --> 20:48.378
I-I keep on thinking
that something's gonna ruin it

20:48.380 --> 20:50.371
and just --
I want to be married already.

20:50.380 --> 20:51.699
[ Smooches ]

20:51.710 --> 20:55.282
[ Light music plays,
indistinct conversations ]

20:55.290 --> 20:56.166
Hey.

20:58.380 --> 20:59.995
Hell, if I'd known
you were coming,

21:00.000 --> 21:03.208
I'd have ordered
for you.
It's my case.

21:03.210 --> 21:05.166
And when you say those things
about the investigation,

21:05.170 --> 21:06.614
you're saying them
about me.

21:06.620 --> 21:08.372
[ Coughs ]
Only you think that, son.

21:08.380 --> 21:09.824
You know it's all smoke.

21:09.830 --> 21:12.412
You know, you know you can't
substantiate any of it.

21:12.420 --> 21:14.456
You just hope people
look at the fire long enough

21:14.460 --> 21:15.996
to forget
that your client is guilty.

21:16.000 --> 21:18.241
I see you do remember
some of what I taught you.

21:18.250 --> 21:20.411
[ Laughs ]

21:22.540 --> 21:25.077
You know what? Just tell
Mom I'm not gonna make
it to brunch this week.

21:25.080 --> 21:27.116
Okay,
now who's being personal?

21:27.120 --> 21:30.203
You crossed that line
when you took on this case.

21:30.210 --> 21:31.495
I never
wanted to be sitting

21:31.500 --> 21:33.377
on opposite sides of the table
from you.

21:33.380 --> 21:35.416
You know that.

21:35.420 --> 21:38.162
You know, maybe it's time
you come to work for me.

21:38.170 --> 21:39.159
Hmm?

21:39.170 --> 21:41.070
We lost our investigator
last week,

21:41.080 --> 21:42.411
so we have an opening.

21:42.420 --> 21:44.615
Don't say no.

21:44.620 --> 21:46.827
Alright, don't say anything
while your anger is so hot.

21:46.830 --> 21:48.115
But I want you
to think about it.

21:48.120 --> 21:49.326
I mean,
we could start you off

21:49.330 --> 21:51.821
at three times
what you're making now --

21:51.830 --> 21:54.116
company car,
vacation time.

21:54.120 --> 21:57.783
And you would not have to live
in that small apartment forever.

21:57.790 --> 22:01.829
Alright, you are, um...
still delusional

22:01.830 --> 22:04.207
if you think I'm gonna accept
an offer like that

22:04.210 --> 22:05.245
after what you did
tonight.

22:05.250 --> 22:07.571
What I did
bought my client his freedom.

22:07.580 --> 22:09.571
I got a call from the
D.A.'s office about an hour ago.

22:09.580 --> 22:10.911
They want to deal.

22:10.920 --> 22:12.956
No.
Kasra would never fold.

22:12.960 --> 22:15.167
Kasra's not
calling the shots.

22:15.170 --> 22:18.207
And there's nothing
the DA. likes less
than a media headache.

22:18.210 --> 22:20.417
So why don't you sit down,
son, relax,

22:20.420 --> 22:23.742
congratulate your old man,
and have a drink with him, huh?

22:23.750 --> 22:25.206
M--

22:31.380 --> 22:32.916
You can relax now, Dex.

22:32.920 --> 22:34.660
Buddy, I'm relaxed.

22:34.670 --> 22:36.114
You're a natural.

22:36.120 --> 22:37.576
Oh, okay, okay.

22:37.580 --> 22:39.457
Good job.
Good job out there.

22:39.460 --> 22:41.667
Can't believe _
Ansel's learning to drive.

22:41.670 --> 22:44.116
That's the most stressful
10 minutes of my life, okay?

22:44.120 --> 22:45.701
Well, you're not making it
easy on him.

22:45.710 --> 22:47.496
Can't imagine learning on
that death trap you call a car.

22:47.500 --> 22:49.456
Okay. Alright.

22:49.460 --> 22:50.745
Where's Grey?

22:50.750 --> 22:52.206
In his office.

22:52.210 --> 22:53.996
He said
he got a bunch of work to do,

22:54.000 --> 22:55.956
but, honestly, I know
what a video game sounds like.

22:55.960 --> 22:57.109
I'm hip.

22:58.670 --> 22:59.910
Grey is, uh...

22:59.920 --> 23:01.535
Regretting this partnership?

23:01.540 --> 23:03.781
Honestly, Tookie,
I don't know why you're not.

23:03.790 --> 23:06.452
What -- What happened to, uh,
"The streets need me"?

23:06.460 --> 23:08.280
I'm getting older.
Mm.

23:08.290 --> 23:09.575
It's time I do something
more legitimate.

23:10.830 --> 23:11.990
You sound like Laura.

23:12.000 --> 23:13.536
Yeah, well,
she's my wife.

23:15.120 --> 23:17.327
You know,
you don't have to, um,

23:17.330 --> 23:20.037
change yourself
to impress someone else.

23:20.040 --> 23:21.371
Why not? She did.

23:21.380 --> 23:22.916
She turned
her whole life around.

23:22.920 --> 23:24.376
I've never _seen her
happier.

23:24.380 --> 23:25.449
I love her, Dex.

23:25.460 --> 23:27.576
I don't want
to be left behind.

23:29.000 --> 23:30.319
Oh. Hey. Claire.

23:30.330 --> 23:31.991
I was just heading out
to update you.

23:32.000 --> 23:34.161
Well, it's no use.
Jenna knows.

23:36.250 --> 23:40.209
She put it together
when she saw you with Zack.

23:40.210 --> 23:41.950
She came at me hard
this morning, and...

23:41.960 --> 23:44.030
I caved.

23:44.040 --> 23:47.112
I've never been any good
at lying to my sister.

23:47.120 --> 23:49.748
Mm. Siblings see through us.
[ Chuckles ]

23:49.750 --> 23:51.160
Yeah.

23:51.170 --> 23:53.320
Anyway,
she lost her mind on me.

23:53.330 --> 23:55.742
She's determined
to marry that man

23:55.750 --> 23:57.786
no matter
what you dig up.

23:57.790 --> 24:00.611
So, this should cover
your time spent.

24:00.620 --> 24:02.372
Thank you.

24:02.380 --> 24:04.996
Uh, for what it's worth,
I didn't find anything.

24:05.000 --> 24:08.322
I think that Zack and Jenna
will be really happy together.

24:08.330 --> 24:09.991
Well,
I pray you're right.

24:10.000 --> 24:12.457
You know, it's so funny.

24:12.460 --> 24:15.452
Most little girls
dream of their own wedding...

24:15.460 --> 24:18.452
[ Chuckling ]
...but I always
dreamt of Jenna's.

24:18.460 --> 24:20.951
I just really want her to have
the fairy tale she deserves.

24:20.960 --> 24:22.996
Ah, especially
after the last one.

24:23.000 --> 24:24.740
Hmm? What last one?

24:26.040 --> 24:29.328
Uh, uh, well,
Jenna was married before.

24:29.330 --> 24:30.570
Right?

24:30.580 --> 24:32.036
No.
Why would you think that?

24:33.620 --> 24:35.110
I don't know.

24:35.120 --> 24:37.611
I must be thinking
of another case.

24:37.620 --> 24:39.167
[ Clears throat ]

24:39.170 --> 24:40.990
What happened?

24:41.000 --> 24:42.956
Your dad
made me sign an NDA.

24:42.960 --> 24:45.997
He finds out I talked, they can
pull my investigator's license.

24:46.000 --> 24:47.206
How long
we known each other?

24:48.880 --> 24:50.666
I wasn't the only one
who was unhappy,

24:50.670 --> 24:52.206
but I was the only one
who complained.

24:52.210 --> 24:53.666
I told HR
I wanted to file a report,

24:53.670 --> 24:55.490
and the next day,
they fired me.

24:55.500 --> 24:57.320
What kind of complaints?

24:57.330 --> 24:59.662
You know your dad
once chucked a stapler
at an assistant's head?

24:59.670 --> 25:01.570
You see that happen?

25:01.580 --> 25:03.036
No.

25:03.040 --> 25:04.667
I can get her to talk
if you keep her name out of it.

25:06.290 --> 25:09.327
I'd love to hear anyone's
complaints about my father.

25:09.330 --> 25:11.286
[Air horn blows ]

25:11.290 --> 25:14.327
[ Crowd cheering ]

25:14.330 --> 25:15.536
As I suspected.

25:15.540 --> 25:17.246
We need to talk.
[ Controller beeps ]

25:17.250 --> 25:19.286
Did you just walk into my office
without knocking?

25:19.290 --> 25:21.110
You never listen to me.
You're distant.

25:21.120 --> 25:22.826
You pay no attention
to my ideas.

25:22.830 --> 25:25.037
I'm an ideas guy, Grey.
I'm trying to make you money.

25:25.040 --> 25:27.076
What are you looking at?

25:27.080 --> 25:28.820
Are you looking
at the gun?

25:28.830 --> 25:30.786
I'm not
looking at the gun.
Are you thinking
of shooting me?

25:30.790 --> 25:32.200
No, I'm not
thinking of shooting you.

25:32.210 --> 25:33.700
Tookie, it's an heirloom
from my grandfather.

25:33.710 --> 25:34.995
It's not a big deal.

25:35.000 --> 25:36.410
But I'll tell you
what is a big deal --

25:36.420 --> 25:38.957
you barging into my office
without knocking.

25:38.960 --> 25:40.825
You're playing video games,
Stripes!
It doesn't matter!

25:40.830 --> 25:42.957
That's the beauty
of owning your own business.

25:42.960 --> 25:44.279
Look, if this partnership's
gonna work --

25:44.290 --> 25:45.325
Partnership?

25:45.330 --> 25:47.787
This is not a partnership,
Tookie!

25:47.790 --> 25:50.167
I let you park your truck
outside of my bar,

25:50.170 --> 25:52.161
and I don't
charge you rent.

25:52.170 --> 25:53.489
You think
you're doing me the favor?

25:53.500 --> 25:55.741
Your chef quit.
You're drowning in bad reviews.

25:55.750 --> 25:57.035
I'm doing the favor here.

25:57.040 --> 25:58.610
Well,
I didn't ask you to come.

25:59.670 --> 26:02.241
Well. [ Chuckles ]

26:02.250 --> 26:03.456
If that's how you feel.

26:03.460 --> 26:04.916
It's not how I feel.
It's the truth.

26:04.920 --> 26:07.036
I didn't ask you to come,
and I don't want you here.

26:08.920 --> 26:10.706
[ Scoffs ] Okay.

26:10.710 --> 26:12.666
Alright.
W-What I'm trying
to say is,

26:12.670 --> 26:15.491
let's just...
finish this trial week

26:15.500 --> 26:17.411
and have a conversation --
Yeah, yeah, you know what?
I'm done here, okay?

26:17.420 --> 26:19.206
Tookie does not
need favors ever!

26:22.710 --> 26:23.779
[ Door slams ]

26:30.170 --> 26:32.286
This is
how we like it, huh?

26:32.290 --> 26:35.282
Quiet. Peaceful.
Intimate.

26:35.290 --> 26:36.450
Am I right?

26:36.460 --> 26:38.416
Why did you hire me?

26:38.420 --> 26:39.705
Why did I hire you?

26:39.710 --> 26:41.166
'Cause you're a hard worker,

26:41.170 --> 26:42.785
you're -- you're smart,
you're good at this.

26:42.790 --> 26:44.576
Tookie is a hard worker.

26:44.580 --> 26:46.536
He's smart.
He's good at this.

26:46.540 --> 26:47.996
Okay, take it easy.

26:48.000 --> 26:49.456
I didn't fire Tookie.

26:49.460 --> 26:51.530
Have you looked
at our PNLs?

26:51.540 --> 26:54.282
PNLs? Since when are you
interested in our financials?

26:54.290 --> 26:56.201
Just look at them.

26:56.210 --> 26:58.826
Slow down, baby

26:58.830 --> 27:01.321
Don't start worrying
about our numbers.

27:03.580 --> 27:05.116
Alright. Fine.
You know what?

27:05.120 --> 27:07.372
We_ sold a few extra cocktails
in the last couple days.

27:07.380 --> 27:09.280
So what? It's a fad.
We're good.

27:09.290 --> 27:10.370
Dude.

27:10.380 --> 27:12.746
When you bringing
those tacos back?

27:12.750 --> 27:14.786
Et tu, Denny?

27:14.790 --> 27:16.746
[ Knock on door ]

27:16.750 --> 27:18.786
Thought you had bridge
on Thursday night.

27:18.790 --> 27:19.779
What -- Ow!

27:19.790 --> 27:21.530
Miles Hoffman,
what have you done?

27:24.790 --> 27:26.246
I told the truth.

27:26.250 --> 27:28.992
You ran with unfounded rumors
to the media.

27:29.000 --> 27:30.740
That investigator
you talked to -- Adam --

27:30.750 --> 27:32.570
he was fired
for drinking on the job.

27:32.580 --> 27:35.492
Of course he has a vendetta
against your father!

27:35.500 --> 27:37.320
The employees who spoke out
were anonymous.

27:37.330 --> 27:38.319
Exactly.

27:38.330 --> 27:40.378
You let that reporter
print slander

27:40.380 --> 27:42.166
that could've
cost people their jobs,

27:42.170 --> 27:43.376
cost your father
his practice.

27:43.380 --> 27:45.109
Got to fight fire
with ﬁre, Ma.

27:45.120 --> 27:46.997
Oh, is that
how it works, huh?

27:47.000 --> 27:49.571
You hate your father's methods,
so you imitate them?

27:49.580 --> 27:50.786
[ Glass thuds ]

27:50.790 --> 27:52.746
At least I'm on
the right side of justice.

27:52.750 --> 27:54.160
No.

27:54.170 --> 27:56.991
You do not get to claim
moral high ground here.

27:57.000 --> 27:58.570
Can you look me in my eye

27:58.580 --> 28:01.538
and tell me that every officer
in your department is honest,

28:01.540 --> 28:03.781
that nobody has ever
looked the other way

28:03.790 --> 28:07.078
or broken procedure
or massaged the evidence ever?

28:08.330 --> 28:11.379
You and your father
are two sides of the same coin.

28:11.380 --> 28:14.452
He never should've
taken this case.

28:14.460 --> 28:17.577
On that, we agree.

28:21.210 --> 28:24.498
_ Your father
is a mountain of a man,

28:24.500 --> 28:28.994
a hero to everyone
who works with him.

28:29.000 --> 28:31.321
Everyone except his sons.

28:33.710 --> 28:35.029
Miles.

28:36.920 --> 28:39.036
Your father loves you.

28:40.790 --> 28:43.452
And all he ever wanted
was your respect.

28:46.710 --> 28:47.950
[ Knock on door ]

28:49.960 --> 28:51.916
[ Door closes ]
It must be bad
if you came all the way here.

28:51.920 --> 28:52.909
Tookie left.

28:52.920 --> 28:55.286
Yeah. I know.
Ansel called.

28:55.290 --> 28:58.111
[ Refrigerator door opens ]
That is
what you wanted, right?

28:58.120 --> 28:59.530
Eh...

28:59.540 --> 29:01.781
I don't know.

29:01.790 --> 29:04.452
Maybe it's possible
I was being a bit of an ass.

29:04.460 --> 29:06.826
Well...
you don't like change.

29:06.830 --> 29:08.786
[ Both laugh ]

29:08.790 --> 29:10.872
No, it's not that.

29:10.880 --> 29:13.371
It's just, this bar is the only
legitimate thing I've ever done,

29:13.380 --> 29:15.200
and then
Tookie was making me wonder

29:15.210 --> 29:17.417
if maybe I hadn't
done it so well, you know?

29:17.420 --> 29:19.536
Yeah, but you have had
a lot on your plate lately.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.496
Yeah, but...

29:21.500 --> 29:24.458
I don't know. Part of me
wanted it that way.

29:24.460 --> 29:27.281
You know, I didn't have to jump
every time Hoffman called,

29:27.290 --> 29:29.030
but I did right away.

29:29.040 --> 29:30.667
[ Chuckles ]

29:30.670 --> 29:32.535
And I keep saying
how much I love The Bad Alibi

29:32.540 --> 29:34.280
and it's my dream,

29:34.290 --> 29:35.917
but if I'm being
totally honest,

29:35.920 --> 29:37.785
I've always had
one foot out the door there.

29:39.040 --> 29:41.326
Uh...well, listen.

29:41.330 --> 29:43.457
If you -- If you want
Tookie back, just talk to him.

29:43.460 --> 29:45.075
He's so weird.
[ Laughs ]

29:45.080 --> 29:46.206
He's a little weird.

29:48.040 --> 29:49.280
I thought your, uh, case
was closed.

29:49.290 --> 29:51.576
What are you doing?
Uh, it was.

29:51.580 --> 29:54.322
_ This woman who's involved
in the investigation, she, um --

29:54.330 --> 29:56.787
she told her fianc
that she lost her first husband,

29:56.790 --> 29:58.200
but I've checked
all the records,

29:58.210 --> 30:00.371
and she's never
been married before.

30:00.380 --> 30:01.950
Well, people lie.

30:01.960 --> 30:04.110
Yes.
Yes, they do.

30:04.120 --> 30:06.327
I-I just kn--
I know how hard it is to --

30:06.330 --> 30:08.412
to pick up
and -- and move on.

30:08.420 --> 30:10.661
You know, he thinks
he's marrying someone

30:10.670 --> 30:12.035
who understands his grief.

30:12.040 --> 30:14.577
Uh, I'm deep
in her social photos,

30:14.580 --> 30:16.741
and I'm --
I'm not seeing any romance.

30:16.750 --> 30:17.785
Mm.

30:19.420 --> 30:21.536
Holy hell.
Hmm?

30:21.540 --> 30:24.373
[Telephone ringing,
indistinct conversations ]

30:34.170 --> 30:35.706
Kasra: Ah.

30:35.710 --> 30:37.746
_ Scales_ balanced back
in our direction last night

30:37.750 --> 30:39.377
with that expos.

30:39.380 --> 30:41.826
No one cares about
the posturing of a man

30:41.830 --> 30:43.741
who abuses his underlings.

30:43.750 --> 30:45.411
Mm. Luclq timing.

30:46.500 --> 30:47.785
Very.

30:47.790 --> 30:49.781
Well,
this should be fun.

30:49.790 --> 30:52.167
I love going in
with a winning hand.

30:57.710 --> 30:58.825
Dex: Hey.

30:58.830 --> 31:00.878
Um, you remember
that hit-and-run case

31:00.880 --> 31:02.996
from last year --
Dahlia Montgomery?

31:03.000 --> 31:04.911
My case? The one
we talked about two days ago?

31:04.920 --> 31:06.319
I don't have Alzheimer's.

31:06.330 --> 31:07.570
Yes, okay.

31:07.580 --> 31:08.911
Well, you said that
the tire tracks on the scene

31:08.920 --> 31:10.160
match a G-Wagen, right?

31:10.170 --> 31:10.989
Yeah.

31:11.000 --> 31:12.956
Okay.
Check this out.

31:12.960 --> 31:15.326
[ Clears throat ]

31:15.330 --> 31:19.369
Okay, so, this is Zack Knight's
current fiance in a G-Wagen

31:19.380 --> 31:21.416
that she hasn't driven
since Dahlia's accident.

31:21.420 --> 31:23.069
S_he's let
the registration lapse.

31:23.080 --> 31:24.786
There's no bill of sale --
nothing.

31:24.790 --> 31:28.203
But she did buy
a brand-new car

31:28.210 --> 31:29.199
three days later.

31:30.380 --> 31:32.450
I-I know_it's not much
on its own,

31:32.460 --> 31:33.950
but this is
a wealthy socialite

31:33.960 --> 31:36.667
who is partying every night
and photographing it,

31:36.670 --> 31:38.285
and then
she just stopped.

31:38.290 --> 31:39.826
She -- She gets clean

31:39.830 --> 31:42.116
immediately
after Dahlia's death.

31:42.120 --> 31:44.202
Circumstantial at best.

31:44.210 --> 31:45.996
Enough to bring her in?

31:46.000 --> 31:47.376
Sure, but I don't see
what good it would do.

31:47.380 --> 31:49.530
Rich kids
always lavwer up quick.

31:49.540 --> 31:50.916
I could try
for a search warrant

31:50.920 --> 31:52.615
on the off chance
she still has the car.

31:52.620 --> 31:54.281
Yeah,
but that's not likely.
No. No.

31:54.290 --> 31:56.246
If she has
any sense at all,

31:56.250 --> 31:58.707
she sold it for parts
or drowned it in Hagg Lake.

31:58.710 --> 31:59.745
[ Sighs ]

31:59.750 --> 32:01.957
So we need a confession.

32:01.960 --> 32:03.780
I told you.

32:03.790 --> 32:06.031
Rich people, lawyers.

32:06.040 --> 32:09.168
Well, that's only a problem
if a cop is asking the question.

32:10.670 --> 32:12.035
Dex.

32:12.040 --> 32:13.780
You're not a cop.

32:13.790 --> 32:15.997
You don't have to read
Miranda rights.

32:16.000 --> 32:17.615
No.
No, I do not.

32:23.540 --> 32:27.533
[ Classical version
of "I Melt with You" plays ]

32:33.790 --> 32:36.202
Got to say,
I'm surprised you own a dress.

32:36.210 --> 32:39.247
Not my choice --
bridesmaid.

32:39.250 --> 32:41.161
What, you --
you got married friends?

32:41.170 --> 32:42.876
I had one once.

32:42.880 --> 32:44.609
Listen,
I'm not gonna lie --

32:44.620 --> 32:46.531
this is gonna be a bit of
a high-wire act, alright?
Mm-hmm.

32:46.540 --> 32:48.531
You got about 20 minutes
before the ceremony starts.

32:48.540 --> 32:50.917
And you need to be discreet
enough so not to tip her off.

32:50.920 --> 32:52.285
But there has to be
Witnesses.

32:52.290 --> 32:54.576
Yeah, I get it.
You've told me a hundred times.

32:54.580 --> 32:57.208
It's the only way the confession
will hold up in court, okay?

32:57.210 --> 32:58.450
Well, she's gonna be
in the bridal suite,

32:58.460 --> 32:59.916
getting ready
with all of her bridesmaids.

32:59.920 --> 33:00.955
That should work,
right?

33:00.960 --> 33:02.575
Sure, if you think
you can get her

33:02.580 --> 33:05.037
to confess to a crime
she already got away With...

33:05.040 --> 33:06.780
in front of
her closest friends...

33:06.790 --> 33:07.870
on her wedding day.

33:07.880 --> 33:09.996
I can be very persuasive.

33:10.000 --> 33:12.992
Yeah, you strike me
as more of an acquired taste.

33:13.000 --> 33:14.376
Fair.
Fair.

33:15.580 --> 33:16.456
Here.

33:16.460 --> 33:17.529
Ooh. What's that?

33:17.540 --> 33:19.872
A second mic? _
A backup battery or something?

33:19.880 --> 33:21.450
It's lipstick, Dex.

33:21.460 --> 33:23.371
It's a wedding.

33:23.380 --> 33:24.824
Right.

33:36.380 --> 33:38.325
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What are you doing here, ma'am?

33:38.330 --> 33:41.288
Hey. Uh, Jenna told me
to meet her in the bridal suite.

33:41.290 --> 33:43.326
I'm one of her closest friends
from St. Louis.

33:43.330 --> 33:45.412
Sorry. Check-in's
at the front entrance.

33:45.420 --> 33:47.069
Yeah,
but she's expecting me.
Go to
the front entrance.

33:47.080 --> 33:48.240
Yeah, okay.

33:48.250 --> 33:49.535
[ Both grunt ]

33:49.540 --> 33:52.168
I'll stop the world
and melt with you

33:52.170 --> 33:54.035
Sorry. Uh...

33:55.500 --> 33:56.660
Hoffman:
Dex, you close?

33:56.670 --> 33:58.570
I'm almost
to the bridal suite.

33:58.580 --> 34:01.538
And it's getting better
all the time

34:01.540 --> 34:04.998
There's nothing
you and I won't do

34:07.580 --> 34:10.572
I'll stop the world
and melt with you

34:19.830 --> 34:21.786
Hoffman, I missed the window.
The wedding started.

34:21.790 --> 34:23.075
That's okay.
Just -- Just pull out.

34:23.080 --> 34:24.411
We'll -- We'll take
another run at her later.

34:24.420 --> 34:25.910
I'm pretty sure
this is my last shot

34:25.920 --> 34:26.955
at getting close
to this family.

34:26.960 --> 34:28.416
Dex.
[ Sighs ]

34:28.420 --> 34:30.115
You said you needed
witnesses, right?

34:30.120 --> 34:31.826
No. No, Dex.

34:31.830 --> 34:33.570
Dex.

34:33.580 --> 34:36.378
Do you, Jenna,
agree to take this man --

34:36.380 --> 34:37.699
[ Door bursts open ]
Dex: Wait! Stop!

34:37.710 --> 34:39.246
Don't do it!

34:39.250 --> 34:40.535
[ Guests murmuring ]

34:40.540 --> 34:42.451
Claire: Ms. Parios!

34:42.460 --> 34:46.419
Uh...why don't we finish
this conversation outside?

34:46.420 --> 34:48.320
No, Jenna,
you're in the program, right?

34:48.330 --> 34:50.412
Doesn't it ask
for you to make amends?

34:50.420 --> 34:52.320
What is going on here?
Claire?

34:52.330 --> 34:54.457
Oh, yeah, uh,
just a small hiccup, my love.

34:54.460 --> 34:56.280
The truth has a way
of coming out.

34:56.290 --> 34:58.167
Zack deserves
to hear it from you.

34:58.170 --> 35:00.377
This woman is insane!
Get her out.

35:00.380 --> 35:02.280
Okay. No, look -- No.

35:02.290 --> 35:04.702
He thinks that he is the reason
that Dahlia's dead, okay?

35:04.710 --> 35:06.826
God! Let go of me!
Stop it!

35:06.830 --> 35:07.615
He blames himself!

35:07.620 --> 35:08.609
Get off!

35:08.620 --> 35:09.826
Would you let --
Claire: Do something!

35:09.830 --> 35:11.991
Stop!
Everybody, stopI

35:12.000 --> 35:13.319
Let her go.

35:15.460 --> 35:18.031
Why does she think you know
something about Dahlia's death?

35:19.080 --> 35:20.911
Because she was there.

35:20.920 --> 35:21.909
[ Guests murmuring ]

35:21.920 --> 35:23.615
Who do you think you are,

35:23.620 --> 35:26.327
bursting in here,
making these insane accusations?

35:26.330 --> 35:28.412
You can't protect me
from this, Claire.

35:28.420 --> 35:30.115
Wh--

35:30.120 --> 35:31.997
[ Murmuring continues ]

35:37.750 --> 35:39.911
I never_should've
gotten in my car.

35:42.250 --> 35:43.660
No.
No, stop talking.

35:43.670 --> 35:45.410
My memories
are all a jumble.

35:45.420 --> 35:48.821
I-I remember being out,
I remember dancing,

35:48.830 --> 35:50.570
and then --

35:50.580 --> 35:54.368
and then there just suddenly
was glass everywhere.

35:54.380 --> 35:57.417
There was just so much glass
and smoke, and --

35:57.420 --> 36:00.958
[Voice breaking ]
...and then I s-saw her.

36:00.960 --> 36:02.996
I didn't know what to do.

36:03.000 --> 36:04.570
I couldn't eat,
couldn't sleep.

36:04.580 --> 36:07.162
I was just
so hollowed out.

36:07.170 --> 36:09.991
And then I --
then I met you, Zack.

36:10.000 --> 36:12.992
And I-I never meant
to fall in love with you.

36:16.460 --> 36:17.779
He needs _
to hear you say it.

36:17.790 --> 36:21.669
Hmm, hmm, hmm

36:21.670 --> 36:24.742
Is there a world --
is...

36:24.750 --> 36:26.115
Hmm, hmm, hmm

36:26.120 --> 36:28.076
Is there a way...

36:28.080 --> 36:29.490
Hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm

36:29.500 --> 36:32.913
Is it possible that
you could learn to forgive me?

36:32.920 --> 36:36.208
Hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm

36:36.210 --> 36:37.165
Neven

36:37.170 --> 36:38.535
Hmm, hmm, hmm

36:38.540 --> 36:40.167
[ Guests murmuring ]

36:40.170 --> 36:43.788
Hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm

36:43.790 --> 36:46.953
I'll stop the world
and melt with you

36:46.960 --> 36:49.497
[ Sobbing ]

36:49.500 --> 36:51.991
You've seen the difference

36:52.000 --> 36:54.707
And it's getting better
all the time

36:58.960 --> 37:01.246
[ Sirens wailing,
police radio chatter ]

37:01.250 --> 37:02.615
I didn't get her
to confess.
You got enough.

37:02.620 --> 37:05.498
A hundred witnesses?
That tape will hold up in court.

37:05.500 --> 37:08.788
Which is great armor
for when her fancy lawyers

37:08.790 --> 37:12.078
start angling
for plea deals.

37:12.080 --> 37:14.116
You want
to talk about it?

37:14.120 --> 37:16.532
The feud
with your father?

37:16.540 --> 37:18.917
Genuinely shocked
you watch the news.

37:18.920 --> 37:21.070
Well,
as a card-carrying member

37:21.080 --> 37:23.492
of the Worst Parents
in the World Club,

37:23.500 --> 37:25.320
uh, booze helps.

37:25.330 --> 37:27.321
I'm not so sure
he's the bad guy in this story.

37:27.330 --> 37:28.160
Miles.

37:28.170 --> 37:29.455
I did a thing.

37:29.460 --> 37:31.997
I-I crossed a line
I never thought I'd cross.

37:32.000 --> 37:33.877
Well,
you made a mistake.

37:33.880 --> 37:36.166
I wouldn't know
what that feels like, um...

37:36.170 --> 37:37.205
[ Chuckles ]

37:37.210 --> 37:39.246
But you can learn
from it.

37:39.250 --> 37:41.878
Is that what you do, Dex?

37:41.880 --> 37:42.949
You just learn from it?

37:42.960 --> 37:43.995
[ Chuckles ]

37:44.000 --> 37:46.992
Do as I say,
not as I do.

37:47.000 --> 37:48.740
See ya.
Alright.

37:49.960 --> 37:52.497
Hey.

37:52.500 --> 37:54.491
You get mine well-done?

37:54.500 --> 37:56.161
It physically pained me
to order it that way,

37:56.170 --> 37:57.706
but, uh -- but, yeah.

37:57.710 --> 37:58.825
[ Chuckles ]

38:01.040 --> 38:03.110
I'm, uh --
I'm sorry, Dad.

38:03.120 --> 38:04.997
What for?

38:06.170 --> 38:09.378
I was behind
that article about you.

38:09.380 --> 38:11.166
I know that, Miles.

38:11.170 --> 38:12.785
And let me tell ya,

38:12.790 --> 38:15.873
I've never been prouder,
son.

38:15.880 --> 38:17.780
You saw what you perceived
to be injustice,

38:17.790 --> 38:19.701
and you did
what you had to do.

38:19.710 --> 38:22.531
It was cheap, Dad.
It was manipulative.

38:22.540 --> 38:24.030
It worked.

38:24.040 --> 38:28.113
You think I do what I do
for fun?

38:28.120 --> 38:29.030
Yeah.

38:29.040 --> 38:30.951
[ Laughs ]

38:30.960 --> 38:32.666
Yeah, well,
it's not not fun.

38:32.670 --> 38:35.070
You know,
the ABA requires me

38:35.080 --> 38:38.709
to do 50 hours of pro bono work
per year.

38:38.710 --> 38:41.167
I do 50 hours per month.

38:41.170 --> 38:44.071
And you know
how I can afford to do that?

38:44.080 --> 38:46.571
By taking money from people
like Charles' father.

38:46.580 --> 38:48.241
That's buying justice.

38:48.250 --> 38:49.660
Yes, it is.

38:49.670 --> 38:52.571
But it's funny how you think
the answer to injustice

38:52.580 --> 38:56.243
is fewer people
getting second chances.

38:56.250 --> 38:58.912
You change your mind about
coming to work for me, son,

38:58.920 --> 39:00.490
_ that door
is always open.

39:00.500 --> 39:02.786
Listen, if I were
to take you up on that offer,

39:02.790 --> 39:05.497
I wouldn't waste the extra money
on a burnt steak.

39:05.500 --> 39:07.377
Hey.
Tastes better that way.

39:07.380 --> 39:09.075
And that's why
no one trusts lawyers.

39:09.080 --> 39:11.287
[ Chuckles ] Hey.

39:13.420 --> 39:16.116
Two tacos especial,
one taco a la Cosgrove.

39:16.120 --> 39:17.667
You're number 18,
my friend.

39:17.670 --> 39:18.955
Thank you.
Next up.

39:18.960 --> 39:20.496
[ Bell clings]

39:22.000 --> 39:23.160
Just a minute.

39:24.790 --> 39:26.917
[ Metal clattering ]

39:29.330 --> 39:30.661
I'm not here to eat.

39:31.880 --> 39:34.576
Yeah, I thought about doing
some kind of a grand gesture,

39:34.580 --> 39:36.320
but, uh...

39:36.330 --> 39:39.037
my idea guy left,
and I got nothin'.

39:39.040 --> 39:40.996
Aww. He called you
his idea guy.

39:41.000 --> 39:42.740
Stay out of this,
Victor!

39:42.750 --> 39:45.036
Can we talk?

39:45.040 --> 39:46.996
I do not forgive you.
Naturally.

39:47.000 --> 39:48.661
I'm not a pushover.

39:48.670 --> 39:50.706
I have too much self-respect
to just come crawling back.

39:50.710 --> 39:51.995
As you should.

39:52.000 --> 39:53.115
Things need to change.
I agree.

39:53.120 --> 39:54.326
Stop yes-manning me.

39:54.330 --> 39:55.536
I'm not y--

39:55.540 --> 39:58.111
I need you. I need
your passion and your ideas.

39:58.120 --> 40:00.247
I need somebody behind the bar
I can trust.

40:00.250 --> 40:01.786
You need a partner?

40:01.790 --> 40:03.280
Let's not
putalabelonit

40:05.120 --> 40:06.951
Deal.

40:06.960 --> 40:08.370
Welcome back.
Bring it in.

40:08.380 --> 40:09.608
What are we doing?

40:09.620 --> 40:11.110
[ Smooches ]

40:13.620 --> 40:15.167
What?

40:15.170 --> 40:17.786
Why are you so weird?
What are you talking about?

40:17.790 --> 40:19.997
It just didn't call for
a face kiss.

40:20.000 --> 40:21.376
It just didn't.
It's a friendly kiss.
I __

40:21.380 --> 40:23.200
Goodbye. Thank you.
See you at work.

40:24.750 --> 40:26.706
[Tattoo needle buzzing ]

40:29.620 --> 40:30.951
[ Buzzing stops ]

40:30.960 --> 40:33.372
We're clone. Finished.

40:33.380 --> 40:34.324
[ Grunts ]

40:34.330 --> 40:36.286
It's perfect.
Mm.

40:36.290 --> 40:39.418
I thought you said
this was gonna hurt.

40:39.420 --> 40:42.162
I'm kidding.
It was...miserable.

40:42.170 --> 40:43.706
[ Chuckles ]
[ Groans ]

40:43.710 --> 40:45.701
Well,
it's on the house.

40:45.710 --> 40:47.280
What? No.

40:47.290 --> 40:48.996
No, no, no, no, no.
I can't accept that.

40:49.000 --> 40:51.958
Please. It's the least
I could do.

40:51.960 --> 40:55.669
You, uh,
found Dahlia's killer,

40:55.670 --> 40:57.570
stopped me from making
the biggest mistake of my life,

40:57.580 --> 40:59.992
and, uh...wel|...
[ Chuckles ]

41:00.000 --> 41:02.457
...you set me free
twice in one day, Dex.

41:02.460 --> 41:04.451
[ Sighs ]

41:09.540 --> 41:10.529
Thanks.

41:10.540 --> 41:12.826
Yeah.

41:12.830 --> 41:16.072
You know, I wish we could've met
under different circumstances.

41:17.420 --> 41:18.569
Yeah.

41:18.580 --> 41:20.491
Maybe someday,
we will, hmm?

41:20.500 --> 41:22.957
[ Vampire Weekend's
"Harmony Hall" plays ]

41:22.960 --> 41:25.326
Until then, thank you.

41:26.790 --> 41:27.745
Yes.

41:29.540 --> 41:32.373
We took a vow in summertime

41:32.380 --> 41:34.996
Now we find ourselves
in late December

41:36.460 --> 41:40.032
Before you ask,
I squeezed these limes myself.

41:40.040 --> 41:41.166
[ Laughs ]
No mix?

41:41.170 --> 41:42.660
Thank God
for small mercies.

41:42.670 --> 41:44.456
Hey,
this is to Ansel --

41:44.460 --> 41:47.577
the new assistant manager
of The Bad Alibi.

41:47.580 --> 41:48.956
What?!

41:48.960 --> 41:50.496
That idea
was all Grey's.

41:50.500 --> 41:52.377
Yeah, buddy, look,
here's the truth.

41:52.380 --> 41:53.950
You know
what's good for this bar

41:53.960 --> 41:55.780
even more
than I know it myself.

41:55.790 --> 41:57.826
And you deserve
the promotion.

41:57.830 --> 41:59.377
To Ansel.
To Ansel.

42:02.250 --> 42:03.820
Mmm!
Tookie,
it pains me to say,

42:03.830 --> 42:06.071
but this is so much better
than the mix.

42:06.080 --> 42:07.536
[ Laughs ] It is.
Hey, guys.

42:07.540 --> 42:09.781
Wow. Thanks.
What are we celebrating?

42:09.790 --> 42:10.950
This guy
right here.

42:10.960 --> 42:11.995
No.

42:12.000 --> 42:13.069
All of us.

42:14.290 --> 42:17.202
Well,
cheers to all of us.

42:17.210 --> 42:18.370
Cheers.

42:18.380 --> 42:21.281
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
